The article states that Todd Gloria, from California, has been appointed as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Harry S Truman Scholarship Foundation. His term will expire on December 10, 2029. Additionally, Tadd M. Johnson from Minnesota has been reappointed as a member of the Board of Trustees of the Morris K. Udall and Stewart L. Udall Foundation, with his term expiring on October 6, 2028. Patricia L. Lee from South Carolina has been nominated as a member of the Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board, replacing Joseph Bruce Hamilton, whose term has expired. Erika L. McEntarfer from the District of Columbia has been nominated as the Commissioner of Labor Statistics at the Department of Labor for a four-year term, replacing William Beach. Jeff Rezmovic from Maryland has been nominated as the Chief Financial Officer at the Department of Homeland Security, replacing Troy D. Edgar. David K. Sing from Hawaii has been nominated as a member of the National Council on the Humanities, replacing Joyce Malcolm, with a term expiring on January 26, 2026. Claudia Slacik from New York has been reappointed as a Director of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation, with a term expiring on December 31, 2026. Finally, Laura Stone from Utah has been nominated as the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of the Marshall Islands.